These menu options define the drawing of ISO-VALUES
LINES in 2D and SURFACES in 3D:
A palette of colors is used from blue (minimum) 
to magenta (maximum)

1: Number of ISO-TEMPERATURES. Default value 10

and the DRAWING MODE
2: REGULAR ISO between the MIN MAX values of the solution
The i-th ISO drawn has for value
    MIN + (i-1)*(MAX-MIN)/(number of ISO-1)

3: DEFINE MIN MAX of ISO
and give after the MIN and MAX of ISO
The i-th ISO drawn will have for value
    MIN + (i-1)*(MAX-MIN)/(number of ISO-1)
   
4: DEFINE VALUES of ISO
and draw these ISOVALUES

5 : COLOR of MESH's EDGES
To define the color of FE edges to locate them

6 : TYPE of LINES of  MESH's EDGES
continuous line or dotted line to draw the edges

7 : COLOR of EDGES of ISO

8 : TYPE of LINES of EDGES of ISO
continuous line or dotted line to draw the edges

19 : REDUCTION % of FACES
to see better the position of edges of faces
or to see the interior of the materials or the other side
A percentage is demanded.
